Sentencas: Bonded compliant seal (BCS) design, which uses a thin S-shaped foil to connect the cell and frame by brazing, is a new sealing method for planar solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Three-dimensional simulation to study the influence of foil thickness on residual stress in the bonded compliant seal design of planar solid oxide fuel cell

Sentencas: This paper studies the brazed residual stress in BCS design of a planar SOFC by three-dimensional finite element method.

Sentencas: The effect of foil thickness on residual stress has been investigated.

Sentencas: The results show that the peak residual stresses are located in S-shaped foil and BNi2 filler metal and have exceeded the yield strength.
